Wait - `"." + File.separator` would be `"./"` on Linux. And `"../"` CONTAINS `"./"`. So `sanitizePath` DOES block `../`!

BUT - what about a path starting with `/`? If path = `/etc/passwd`, `sanitizePath` doesn't block it (no dots). Then `staticRoot.resolve("/etc/passwd")` would return `/etc/passwd` (absolute path override)!

